Web Apps & Tools Utilized for Leverage

----------------------
|  Malware Analysis  |
----------------------
######################################################################################################################################################################################################################################

## Static Analysis Tools  
*Tools for examining malware without execution, focusing on binary structure, disassembly, and signatures.*

- https://mh-nexus.de/en/hxd/                      ***Hex editor for inspecting and modifying binary files.***
- https://ghidra-sre.org/                          ***Software reverse engineering (SRE) suite of tools.***
- https://ntcore.com/explorer-suite/               ***Collection of utilities for analyzing PE (Portable Executable) files.***
- https://systeminformer.sourceforge.io/downloads  ***Advanced system monitoring tool for inspecting running processes.***  
- https://www.winitor.com/download                 ***Windows forensic analysis tool for deeper inspection.***  
- https://hex-rays.com/ida-pro/                    ***Powerful disassembler and debugger used for reverse engineering binaries.***

######################################################################################################################################################################################################################################

## Dynamic Analysis Tools  
*Tools that execute malware in a controlled environment to observe behavior, system modifications, and network activity.*

- https://procdot.com/              ***Visualizes process interactions and system calls during execution.***  
- https://www.joesandbox.com/       ***Automated malware analysis providing in-depth behavioral reports.***  
- https://www.hybrid-analysis.com/  ***Cloud-based sandbox for dynamic malware analysis with threat intelligence.***
- https://x64dbg.com/               ***Open-source debugger for analyzing Windows executables (both 32-bit and 64-bit).***
--- Scylla Hide can also be used in combination with the above as a plugin to hide it from Malware -> https://github.com/x64dbg/ScyllaHide

######################################################################################################################################################################################################################################

## Threat Intelligence & Malware Databases  
- https://www.virustotal.com/gui/  ***Aggregates antivirus scan results and provides behavioral analysis.***  
- https://urlhaus.abuse.ch/        ***Tracks and shares active malware distribution URLs.***  

######################################################################################################################################################################################################################################

## Malware Analysis Environment

- https://remnux.org/   ***Linux distribution preloaded with tools for malware analysis and reverse engineering.***  

######################################################################################################################################################################################################################################

------------------------------
| Stages of Malware Analysis |
------------------------------

1. Fully Automated Analysis
File Interactions – File creation, modification, or deletion.
Network Activity – Remote connections or payload downloads.
Process Behavior – Child processes or code injection.
System Changes – Registry edits, persistence, or service creation.

2. Static Property Analysis
String Extraction – Finds readable text like file paths, IPs, or commands.
Header Analysis – Determines file type, structure, and timestamps.
Entropy Assessment – Detects packing or obfuscation attempts.
Import/Export Inspection – Identifies functions used by the file.

3. Interactive Behaviour Analysis
Behavior Testing – Triggers functionality with specific inputs.
Evasion Detection – Identifies anti-sandbox and anti-VM tactics.
System Monitoring – Tracks file, registry, and network activity.

4. Manual Code Reversing
Code Decryption – Unpacking obfuscated logic.
Capability Analysis – Identifying core malware functions.
Function & Algorithm Review – Examining encryption and anti-analysis techniques.
Artifact Identification – Extracting IOCs for detection and mitigation.

--- Lenny Zeltser, 2025, How You Can Start Learning Malware Analysis, Sans.org ---
